therefore, you have to turn the subjective into water.

247
00:25:04,640 --> 00:25:07,900
Like you mix water in water and wine in wine.

248
00:25:09,710 --> 00:25:11,250
Why? Did I do wrong?

249
00:25:11,250 --> 00:25:13,790
Hm...

250
00:25:29,300 --> 00:25:31,950
It's the same.

251
00:25:31,950 --> 00:25:34,830
I don't know what this is talking about.

252
00:25:40,470 --> 00:25:45,570
Do you think I wasted this paper to see you write nonsense?

253
00:25:45,570 --> 00:25:51,380
I assigned this task to see what kind of world you are dreaming of.

254
00:25:51,380 --> 00:25:57,310
But surprisingly, you don't have any thoughts about your world.

255
00:26:01,180 --> 00:26:07,920
Nevertheless, who are the owners of this emptiness and this thoughtlessness?

256
00:26:14,670 --> 00:26:16,900
Kim Ji Dwi and Kim Seon Woo. Did you guys plan to fail?

257
00:26:16,900 --> 00:26:20,750
Or is there a more profound answer beyond my imagination?

258
00:26:20,750 --> 00:26:25,980
I don't think that old man, Noza (author of Tao Te Ching), would have expressed himself in writing only.

259
00:26:26,990 --> 00:26:32,760
"Moo-wi" is not doing something forcefully. Isn't that what it means?

260
00:26:35,410 --> 00:26:37,660
Do you think that too?

261
00:26:38,420 --> 00:26:41,890
I wouldn't be able to write what I think with the limited letters I know,

262
00:26:41,890 --> 00:26:45,370
so I want to say the answer aloud.

263
00:26:46,780 --> 00:26:48,400
Yo. (forgot to use formal tone)

264
00:26:48,400 --> 00:26:50,990
Then, who wants to go first?

265
00:26:50,990 --> 00:26:53,200
- I will...
- I will start first.

266
00:26:57,900 --> 00:27:01,530
Then you who gave me a blank paper, go first.

267
00:27:03,930 --> 00:27:08,630
This Silla's law is based on the Bone Rank System.

268
00:27:08,630 --> 00:27:11,490
Water, "Soo." Flow, "Geo."

269
00:27:11,490 --> 00:27:16,720
The law follows wherever the water flows. In other words, it shouldn't force its way out. The law flows naturally like water.

270
00:27:16,720 --> 00:27:19,920
But not everything has a waterway.

271
00:27:19,920 --> 00:27:26,830
Some land is arid, and some land is rich. To flow and flow along the natural path,

272
00:27:26,830 --> 00:27:32,340
it results in a harmony and an appealing power without offending others.

273
00:27:32,340 --> 00:27:35,820
That should be the king's rule and the king's way.

274
00:27:40,000 --> 00:27:41,830
That's bullsh*t.

275
00:27:44,340 --> 00:27:48,990
"The nobility is structured on top of the lowly, and the high class stands up on a base of the low class."

276
00:27:48,990 --> 00:27:52,020
I think this is the worse bullsh*t

277
00:27:53,430 --> 00:27:58,170
You dare call the Tao Te Ching nonsense?

278
00:27:58,170 --> 00:28:03,480
Waterways flow from high to low. Then,

279
00:28:03,480 --> 00:28:08,520
where can water at the bottom find its path?

280
00:28:10,390 --> 00:28:13,070
A road where the low can become the high.

281
00:28:13,070 --> 00:28:15,340
The road is not only for the waterway that flows from above to below,

282
00:28:15,340 --> 00:28:20,470
but also for the waterway which must be dampened through tortuous effort.

283
00:28:20,470 --> 00:28:24,660
I couldn't find that answer in the Tao Te Ching.

284
00:28:26,850 --> 00:28:29,780
No path was born to be a path from the beginning.

285
00:28:29,780 --> 00:28:32,780
Someone has had to walk on first to become a path,

286
00:28:32,780 --> 00:28:38,680
and after the soil is molded and formed, then a waterway will form for the first time.

287
00:28:39,640 --> 00:28:44,590
If it is law to turn away the dry land (the lowly), and if that's the king's waterway, that king...

288
00:28:44,590 --> 00:28:49,130
That king shouldn't continue as king.

289
00:28:58,190 --> 00:29:01,980
Pass, fail,

290
00:29:01,980 --> 00:29:08,720
Pass, fail, pass, fail.

291
00:29:09,530 --> 00:29:13,650
Pass, fail, pass.

292
00:29:13,650 --> 00:29:16,260
- Hey!
- You startled me.

293
00:29:16,260 --> 00:29:17,990
Do you think he passed?

294
00:29:17,990 --> 00:29:19,930
Don't you think you're asking too much?

295
00:29:19,930 --> 00:29:24,420
Have a conscience! He's just started to learn how to write.

296
00:29:24,420 --> 00:29:26,200
Right?

297
00:29:27,350 --> 00:29:33,800
Ah, just stop please. Why are you doing that to those poor herbs?

298
00:29:34,710 --> 00:29:37,390
Oh my gosh, I did this?

299
00:29:38,460 --> 00:29:40,260
I'm sorry.

300
00:29:42,250 --> 00:29:43,650
Pass...

301
00:29:43,650 --> 00:29:46,650
Kim Ki Bo, fail.

302
00:29:46,650 --> 00:29:49,600
Kim Shin, fail.

303
00:29:49,600 --> 00:29:53,240
Kim Jang Hyeon, fail.

304
00:29:53,240 --> 00:29:55,050
Seok Han Seong

305
00:29:57,790 --> 00:30:02,250
You copied all three chapters of the "Tao Te Ching." It's fail for you too.

306
00:30:02,250 --> 00:30:03,330
Ah, why.

307
00:30:03,330 --> 00:30:07,420
Kim Soo Ho, fail.

308
00:30:07,420 --> 00:30:10,440
Kim Yeo Wool, fail.

309
00:30:11,360 --> 00:30:13,030
Park Ban Ryu.

310
00:30:16,350 --> 00:30:17,870
- Pass.
- Wow

311
00:30:19,490 --> 00:30:21,480
Kim Ji Dwi.

312
00:30:26,770 --> 00:30:28,620
You have passed.

313
00:30:30,290 --> 00:30:37,320
Not because I like your answer, but because it is based on the "Tao Te Ching."

314
00:30:39,010 --> 00:30:42,290
Kim Seon Woo.

315
00:30:45,040 --> 00:30:46,940
You have failed.

316
00:30:46,940 --> 00:30:54,670
It isn't that I didn't like your answer, but I asked you to base your answer on the "Tao Te Ching."

317
00:30:54,670 --> 00:30:59,700
You called the "Tao Te Ching" rubbish, so because of that, I cannot pass you.

318
00:31:02,660 --> 00:31:05,680
It's a pity that we're left with so much kindling paper.

319
00:31:06,330 --> 00:31:11,230
Today's lecture ends here. Everyone may go out.

320
00:31:24,360 --> 00:31:31,680
Hey. You only have two chances from now. Didn't I tell you the result would be the same?

321
00:31:31,680 --> 00:31:36,090
You will have to use your vain effort twice and get kicked out.

322
00:31:37,680 --> 00:31:39,510
Go.

323
00:31:47,460 --> 00:31:55,570
If it is law to turn away the dry land, and if that's the king's waterway, that king

324
00:31:55,570 --> 00:31:59,390
shouldn't continue as king.

325
00:31:59,390 --> 00:32:02,120
Ah, he's such a tough cookie.

326
00:32:03,200 --> 00:32:05,930
Why did that guy fail?

327
00:32:06,630 --> 00:32:11,140
Aigoo, who is this? Is it my fake nephew?

328
00:32:11,140 --> 00:32:16,130
So, you said you would bring down the Queen Dowager. Is that going well?

329
00:32:16,130 --> 00:32:18,640
Originally, did you not have the same thoughts as that guy?

330
00:32:18,640 --> 00:32:22,980
You hate the arrogance of the high officials and think of the subjects first.

331
00:32:22,980 --> 00:32:26,980
What king could look up from below?

332
00:32:26,980 --> 00:32:31,240
The hidden king would be able to, don't you think?

333
00:32:31,240 --> 00:32:36,570
You seem to anticipate a lot from the king who has no face.

334
00:32:37,290 --> 00:32:43,090
Did you not as well, Poong Wol Joo? So, isn't that why you oppose the regency?

335
00:32:44,780 --> 00:32:47,720
What would I know about the King?

336
00:32:47,720 --> 00:32:51,140
A child, who couldn't protect his body and was busy hiding,

337
00:32:51,140 --> 00:32:54,960
what can he do once he returns?

338
00:32:54,960 --> 00:33:02,690
The young and useless king will not be able to do anything among the deceitful officials.

339
00:33:03,700 --> 00:33:09,660
There is no longer a reason for the Queen to stay in power. And the unprepared king

340
00:33:09,660 --> 00:33:16,830
will be an anguish for this Silla. So that's why I made Hwarang.

341
00:33:18,090 --> 00:33:24,520
Silla's future, the future must be protected.

342
00:33:30,290 --> 00:33:36,250
If you figure out a way to protect Silla even with the Queen dragged down,

343
00:33:36,250 --> 00:33:43,460
find me again then. Anyway, I was having a hard time catching fish even without you. Now you made it worse.

344
00:33:47,720 --> 00:33:49,550
You can go.

345
00:34:03,350 --> 00:34:04,990
Fail?

346
00:34:05,700 --> 00:34:06,530
Kim Ji Dwi.

347
00:34:09,080 --> 00:34:11,070
What is this?

348
00:34:11,070 --> 00:34:16,150
No way. This is a blank sheet. Why is it a pass? But my brother who wrote several, is a fail?

349
00:34:16,150 --> 00:34:24,050
Oh! I've got it! This is the so-called corruption in Hwarang.

350
00:34:24,050 --> 00:34:26,360
I just can't let this go.

351
00:34:27,780 --> 00:34:31,610
How could this be? Aigoo.

352
00:34:32,440 --> 00:34:37,920
Ah, okay. I heard from Pi Joo Gyoo that you are working here. I'm busy with some personal issue.

353
00:34:37,920 --> 00:34:40,450
How could you really do this?

354
00:34:40,450 --> 00:34:43,940
Abuse of powerful one towards the weak. A true bone is innocent! A nobody is guilty.

355
00:34:43,940 --> 00:34:46,390
You pampered your nephew too much.

356
00:34:46,390 --> 00:34:49,500
Ah, what are you taking about? Move.

357
00:34:49,500 --> 00:34:56,150
When a blank sheet is a pass, how can this be a fail with an elaborate answer written by a beginner in writing?

358
00:34:56,150 --> 00:35:02,150
Ah, that, the assignment was on "Tao Te Ching," but that guy... Anyway, move!

359
00:35:02,150 --> 00:35:06,230
Enough! If you are like this, I cannot overlook this.

360
00:35:06,230 --> 00:35:09,420
So what do you want?

361
00:35:09,420 --> 00:35:13,330
The research on the young noblemen, you remember that, right?

362
00:35:13,330 --> 00:35:19,970
I will tell to each official, how at Poong Wol Joo's request, I conducted a secret investigation.

363
00:35:19,970 --> 00:35:22,570
Whatever you want!

364
00:35:22,570 --> 00:35:27,010
Ah, ha! You don't know. This isn't a simple issue, is it?

365
00:35:27,010 --> 00:35:33,330
They'll say that it is illegal monitoring and that we should annihilate Hwarang. Then, the Queen will be in trouble, too.

366
00:35:33,330 --> 00:35:35,000
Just!

367
00:35:45,270 --> 00:35:51,300
So, the girl with 100 talents, what do we want?

368
00:35:53,100 --> 00:35:57,730
Don't do that next time. Do you understand?

369
00:36:02,350 --> 00:36:05,210
It looks like I can finally go...

370
00:36:07,520 --> 00:36:10,290
Ah, I need to go inside.

371
00:36:24,090 --> 00:36:26,300
It's the silver you lent me last time.

372
00:36:30,460 --> 00:36:34,060
Now that there's nothing left, let's not cross paths again.

373
00:36:40,250 --> 00:36:44,530
But why were you going to learn how to write from me?

374
00:36:44,530 --> 00:36:49,640
Apparently you must have some strong support for you to be able to submit a blank sheet and receive a pass.

375
00:36:49,640 --> 00:36:53,590
I wasn't able to help out my brother because of you and he failed.

376
00:36:53,590 --> 00:36:57,360
I should have supported him until the end. It's all ruined because of you.

377
00:36:57,360 --> 00:37:02,850
So you're saying that you couldn't be concerned about your brother because you were concerned about me?

378
00:37:02,850 --> 00:37:05,780
Those words make me feel the best out of all the things you have said.

379
00:37:05,780 --> 00:37:07,290
I didn't mean to say it that way.

380
00:37:07,290 --> 00:37:10,370
Well, that can't be considered nothing.

381
00:37:10,370 --> 00:37:14,980
That thing happened between the two of us, so it can't be considered nothing.

382
00:37:15,630 --> 00:37:20,600
It's not because we kissed. I felt bad for you.

383
00:37:21,160 --> 00:37:25,770
You seemed lonely and didn't know where to fit in.

384
00:37:25,770 --> 00:37:28,120
I was like that too...

385
00:37:29,140 --> 00:37:31,380
since I've been lonely before.

386
00:37:34,470 --> 00:37:39,290
That's why I was like that. Now there won't be an incident like that ever again.

387
00:37:40,120 --> 00:37:45,600
What do I have to do? What do I have to do for you to look at me?

388
00:37:47,530 --> 00:37:50,790
When I look at you, I go crazy because I feel like I become nothing.

389
00:37:50,790 --> 00:37:55,290
- Don't mess with me—
- I don't know who I am or what I'm doing when I think about you.

390
00:37:56,170 --> 00:37:57,570
I don't.

391
00:38:19,430 --> 00:38:21,760
Can we go inside today?

392
00:38:25,490 --> 00:38:30,340
This person, how many times has this been? Call the Chief Officer at once!

393
00:38:45,080 --> 00:38:48,330
Let's have a glass of red wine in thirty years.

394
00:38:48,330 --> 00:38:51,870
But this Wi Hwa Gong person!

395
00:38:51,870 --> 00:38:56,500
Let's go. There will be another opportunity next time.

396
00:38:56,500 --> 00:39:00,520
- Yeong Sil Gong...
- I only came here to see someone I wanted to see.

397
00:39:00,520 --> 00:39:05,250
Please let us in next time.

398
00:39:05,250 --> 00:39:07,590
Let's go.

399
00:39:07,590 --> 00:39:12,020
This is not the only place with someone I want to see.

400
00:39:43,230 --> 00:39:46,040
It's been a while, Ahn Ji Gong.

401
00:39:48,280 --> 00:39:54,320
I heard you found your son. Congratulations.

402
00:39:54,320 --> 00:39:57,420
I heard that he is a Hwarang.

403
00:39:57,420 --> 00:40:02,170
He is the Hwarang that the Queen Dowager picked herself?

404
00:40:02,170 --> 00:40:06,780
You are weak and your kidney function is getting worse,

405
00:40:07,830 --> 00:40:10,600
so you will have to be careful with your regimen.

406
00:40:10,600 --> 00:40:15,620
For now, I will do moxibustion and do acupuncture. I will prescribe medicine.

407
00:40:17,120 --> 00:40:20,090
You should get a servant to get it.

408
00:40:20,090 --> 00:40:26,290
It will be something much better than what I have.

409
00:40:28,230 --> 00:40:35,520
They say that a woman's jealousy can call for snow, even in summer.

410
00:40:37,270 --> 00:40:41,710
A lot of time has passed.

411
00:40:41,710 --> 00:40:46,520
But even time failed to resolve the woman's resentment.

412
00:40:46,520 --> 00:40:50,140
Don't you know that fact the best?

413
00:40:51,120 --> 00:40:53,980
I think

414
00:40:53,980 --> 00:40:58,110
we have the same point of view.

415
00:41:01,320 --> 00:41:04,240
Does Pervert Gong really like me?

416
00:41:04,240 --> 00:41:10,280
He's not bad. He's the nephew of the Chief Officer, and it doesn't look like he's from a household that has nothing.

417
00:41:10,280 --> 00:41:12,950
If he studied in the West, then he probably has a lot of knowledge.

418
00:41:12,950 --> 00:41:16,390
His appearance... Even if I look at him objectively, he's good.

419
00:41:19,990 --> 00:41:24,230
What am I saying? Especially on a day like this. I'm definitely crazy to be thinking these things.

420
00:41:24,230 --> 00:41:26,840
- What kind of day is it today?
- You scared me.

421
00:41:28,180 --> 00:41:30,910
It's just well...

422
00:41:30,910 --> 00:41:32,970
Nothing much.

423
00:41:34,760 --> 00:41:40,740
Return safely. Only go on big roads, and go with Pi Joo Gyoo.

424
00:41:43,480 --> 00:41:49,160
I heard everyone failed, so don't be too upset.

425
00:41:49,160 --> 00:41:53,040
It's the Chief Officer's fault for assigning a question like that. It's not your fault.

426
00:41:53,040 --> 00:41:58,120
And in my opinion, you did pretty well.

427
00:42:07,280 --> 00:42:12,280
I got it, so go.

428
00:42:12,280 --> 00:42:17,070
It's Mother's memorial day.

429
00:42:19,010 --> 00:42:22,370
I said today is Mother's memorial day.

430
00:42:24,950 --> 00:42:30,850
Don't worry. I've prepared her memorial rite by myself every year. I will tell her that I met you during the rite and she'll be happy.

431
00:42:30,850 --> 00:42:34,530
You have to be here, so I'll do it.

432
00:42:40,860 --> 00:42:43,710
Is this... a vegetable side dish?

433
00:42:43,710 --> 00:42:48,150
It tastes good. It feels like it's homemade.

434
00:42:48,150 --> 00:42:50,470
Why are you here?

435
00:42:50,470 --> 00:42:54,670
I'm comfortable here. And it's even. Six.

436
00:42:56,390 --> 00:42:59,520
I warned you that you can't endure staying here, right?

437
00:42:59,520 --> 00:43:04,970
Since you already got a fail, it doesn't seem like you will be able to stay here for long.

438
00:43:04,970 --> 00:43:10,850
Are you that happy that you passed? I think Dog-Bird had the best answer out of the right answers.

439
00:43:10,850 --> 00:43:11,900
What?

440
00:43:11,900 --> 00:43:15,790
Everyone else thinks that way, no?

441
00:43:22,880 --> 00:43:25,100
Is something called a memorial that important?

442
00:43:26,740 --> 00:43:29,000
Is it that important?

443
00:43:29,000 --> 00:43:30,880
Whose memorial is it?

444
00:43:34,160 --> 00:43:36,450
She said it's my mother's.

445
00:43:38,290 --> 00:43:41,660
Then shouldn't you go home? The assignment is over too.

446
00:43:51,280 --> 00:43:53,280
It's her memorial day.

447
00:43:54,500 --> 00:43:57,880
I said today is Mother's memorial day

448
00:44:03,790 --> 00:44:09,280
This is no different from prison. The assignment is over, so why do I have to sleep with you guys?

449
00:44:09,280 --> 00:44:11,300
Then you can leave.

450
00:44:14,510 --> 00:44:18,990
You said it's like prison. And you'll have to leave for the memorial.

451
00:44:20,010 --> 00:44:25,850
I'm warning you guys. Don't do unnecessary things and get me into trouble.

452
00:44:25,850 --> 00:44:29,410
What are you cooking up? You're not the type of person to do something without a backup plan.

453
00:44:29,410 --> 00:44:33,030
I played little tricks.

454
00:44:36,320 --> 00:44:38,060
What is this?

455
00:44:38,060 --> 00:44:42,860
It's something my mother prepared when I came here.

456
00:44:42,860 --> 00:44:46,280
It's a precious medicinal wine from the West.

457
00:44:46,280 --> 00:44:49,370
She told me to gift it to the Chief Officer and the Master.

458
00:44:50,650 --> 00:44:52,540
Thank you.

459
00:44:54,960 --> 00:44:57,050
It's not a medicinal wine, but a pass-out wine

460
00:44:57,050 --> 00:45:00,580
It's so strong that just one drink will make the whole body relax

461
00:45:00,580 --> 00:45:01,950
Ah, it's hot!

462
00:45:01,950 --> 00:45:06,630
And if you have two drinks, then you wouldn't recognize your parents. "The end" wine.

463
00:45:06,630 --> 00:45:10,510
So you're saying this place is completely defenseless?

464
00:45:10,510 --> 00:45:13,730
If you want to leave you can leave, and if you want to stay you can stay.

465
00:45:15,070 --> 00:45:19,560
But it might be best to leave since everyone is going to be responsible.

466
00:45:19,560 --> 00:45:21,760
Do you think this crazy act makes sense?

467
00:45:21,760 --> 00:45:25,950
If you don't like it, you can tell them, but we'll be outside by then.

468
00:45:27,690 --> 00:45:29,090
What do you want to do?

469
00:45:30,300 --> 00:45:31,880
I'll have to leave.

470
00:45:34,550 --> 00:45:37,560
Don't you have a reason to leave?

471
00:45:53,830 --> 00:45:57,550
What is this? Did the wine not work?

472
00:46:00,720 --> 00:46:04,450
Did it not go through? I definitely gave him a bottle.

473
00:46:04,450 --> 00:46:07,470
It's a wine that you can't resist even if you smell it.

474
00:46:11,610 --> 00:46:16,010
Instead of it being the end for the wine, it's going to be the end for us!

475
00:46:22,340 --> 00:46:23,740
What is this?

476
00:46:36,190 --> 00:46:41,180
What did I tell you? I said it's "The End" wine.

477
00:46:43,800 --> 00:46:46,230
- Let's go.
- Let's go, let's go, let's go.

478
00:47:05,520 --> 00:47:07,910
These guys, seriously!

479
00:47:16,490 --> 00:47:20,320
Let's meet here at dawn and go back in together.

480
00:47:20,320 --> 00:47:21,960
Let's go, let's go.

481
00:47:42,680 --> 00:47:44,790
Location sponsored by Korean Folk Village

482
00:47:50,090 --> 00:47:54,260
You scared me to death. Now are you going to be wandering at night?

483
00:47:54,260 --> 00:47:58,090
Please don't play around with those kids. You still have your royal position.

