00:47:58,090 --> 00:48:00,770
Stop nagging and just lead my way.

485
00:48:00,770 --> 00:48:02,720
Where are you going in the middle of the night?

486
00:48:04,710 --> 00:48:06,330
Home.

487
00:48:27,020 --> 00:48:30,470
Your Highness, it's that flower again.

488
00:48:30,470 --> 00:48:33,530
It's a flower that doesn't bloom within the palace.

489
00:48:54,370 --> 00:48:56,490
What do you think you're doing?

490
00:48:57,580 --> 00:48:59,920
I'm just sitting in my seat for a bit.

491
00:48:59,920 --> 00:49:04,430
Do you think you have the strength to be in that seat?

492
00:49:04,430 --> 00:49:11,530
No. Just as you said, I'm too small and weak.

493
00:49:11,530 --> 00:49:17,180
It's a relief that you realized that. Then, leave the Hwarang immediately.

494
00:49:17,970 --> 00:49:22,630
Once you leave Hwarang quietly, I'll take care of the rest.

495
00:49:22,630 --> 00:49:27,620
The more I wait for it, the stronger you get.

496
00:49:28,520 --> 00:49:31,180
A small child can't walk from the beginning.

497
00:49:31,180 --> 00:49:36,220
Step by step. He has to get strength in his legs and experience what it's like to fall

498
00:49:36,220 --> 00:49:38,610
to finally know how to walk.

499
00:49:38,610 --> 00:49:41,800
No path was born to be a path from the beginning..

500
00:49:41,800 --> 00:49:45,090
Someone has had to walk there first for it to become a path,

501
00:49:45,090 --> 00:49:51,250
and after the soil is molded and formed, then a waterway will form for the first time.

502
00:49:55,330 --> 00:49:57,480
I need to walk in order to

503
00:49:58,810 --> 00:50:01,930
go on the King's path.

504
00:50:03,710 --> 00:50:09,690
I will become stronger by being in Hwarang, Mother.

505
00:50:35,630 --> 00:50:39,590
I met my brother whom I have been searching for all that time.

506
00:50:39,590 --> 00:50:42,530
But it's still just the two of us for the memorial, Father.

507
00:50:42,530 --> 00:50:44,200
♬ Your aching heart displays everything♬

508
00:50:44,200 --> 00:50:47,520
But since we found Brother,

509
00:50:47,520 --> 00:50:51,720
don't feel sorry towards mother anymore.

510
00:50:51,720 --> 00:50:54,840
Okay. I'll do that.

511
00:50:56,060 --> 00:50:58,910
I'm curious about something.

512
00:50:58,910 --> 00:51:02,320
Did something happen to Brother?

513
00:51:02,960 --> 00:51:09,420
You see, when Brother first came here, he barely survived after almost dying.

514
00:51:09,420 --> 00:51:15,950
He definitely went through something tough, but it's a bit much to ask him about it directly.

515
00:51:15,950 --> 00:51:22,640
♬ I'm afraid the more I try to wipe it out, the more I will be left yearning♬

516
00:51:22,640 --> 00:51:33,550
♬ So I can't let it go ♬

517
00:51:35,720 --> 00:51:44,040
♬ Although you and I became tears for each other♬

518
00:51:44,040 --> 00:51:51,630
♬ After time passed on a bright day♬

519
00:51:51,630 --> 00:51:56,940
♬ when we just held each other and it was just like a dream♬

520
00:51:56,940 --> 00:52:00,550
In the end, you end up here?

521
00:52:00,550 --> 00:52:06,940
♬ I remember that time then.♬

522
00:52:09,700 --> 00:52:11,700
Whoa, whoa, whoa.

523
00:52:21,260 --> 00:52:24,070
Wait here. I'll go get the servant.

524
00:52:24,070 --> 00:52:27,310
It's late, so why call a servant?

525
00:52:27,310 --> 00:52:29,760
Let's not make a scene.

526
00:52:31,340 --> 00:52:32,800
Yes.

527
00:52:51,950 --> 00:52:56,180
Oh, they're so handsome! So handsome!

528
00:52:56,180 --> 00:53:01,490
You said you missed the outside air. What's your reaction to those women?

529
00:53:03,260 --> 00:53:05,650
Each one of those is half-ripe,

530
00:53:08,090 --> 00:53:10,080
